name: Skuhl
tweet: @jojoincolorado @LilJungMoney @AcademicChatter Nope, not semantics. Double depression has a much higher risk of poor outcomes/suicide than either alone. Major depression is very distinct...slowed physiology, hopelessness about future, self. Pdd is a mild depr that never lets up. Mdd is covid. Pdd is bad allergies yr round

name: Skuhl
tweet: @LilJungMoney Oh, persistent depre dis. The answer is in the name. Mdd comes and goes. For many the person returns to normal affect, full range of emotion is available. But in pdd  the best they ever do is mild depression...no "normal". Mdd gets layered on top of pdd for double depression.

name: Catherine Griwkowsky
tweet: Dysthymia (I think it's also now called persistent depressive disorder) is a chronic, mild depression that last for a long period of time (years). A double depression (which kind of sounds hilarious to me, tbh) is when those symptoms of depression get much worse.

name: vinegar queen
